                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1094.</note>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-15T00:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1914, 12 midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <p>I am informed Bordas’ mission results in peaceable understanding with Arias which
                    means that constitutional convention will proceed to enact your reforms
                    including new election law. Governmental program includes an election of
                    president to succeed Bordas on June 30th, the real date when the Caceres term
                    ended, instead of April 13th. I understand this is constitutional and not
                    inconsistent with congressional decree which pronounced choice of Bordas.
                    President returns early this week when I can give Department details of
                    situation. Believe revolution again averted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
